threads.title: 820-3437-B not powering
threads.message:
Hi guys,

Got a 3437-B which had fluid damage around U1950. Cleaned area and replaced U1950. Getting green light but no fan spin. Rails so far as follows:

PPBUS_G3H = 8.56V
PP3V3_S5     =  3.0V
PP5V_S5        = 5.0V
PP3V3_S4       = 0V

Struggling to understand on schematic where S4 rails will come from - and is the S5 rail being lower than 3.3V relevant (only 3.0V)?

threads.title: 820-3437-B not powering
threads.message:
You may have corrosion around U7501.
Post diode mode to ground at L7560.

Do you get 3V3_SUS?

threads.title: 820-3437-B not powering
threads.message:
Diode mode to ground at L7560 = 0.344v

3v3_SUS is 0v

U7501 looks clean (but also fresh solder on test points in the area so likely board has been repaired previously)

threads.title: 820-3437-B not powering
threads.message: Check S5_PWRGD, PM_DSW_PWRGD, PM_BATLOW_L, SMC_ADAPTER_EN and all PCH's RTC signals.
